3.
Information for Colorado Residents
(a)
As of July 1, 2023, Colorado residents acting as consumers have the following rights under the Colorado Privacy Act, subject to the conditions therein:
(i)
Confirm whether or not EXPTIONAL is processing the consumer's personal data and to access such data;
(ii)
Correct inaccuracies in the consumer's personal data, taking into account the nature of the personal data and the purposes of the processing of the consumer's personal data;
(iii)
Delete personal data concerning the consumer;
(iv)
Obtain a copy of the consumer's personal data that the consumer previously provided to EXPTIONAL in a portable, and to the extent technically feasible, readily usable format that allows the consumer to transmit the data to another entity without hindrance; and
(v)
Opt-out of the processing of the consumer's personal data for the purposes of: (i) targeted advertising, (ii) the sale of personal data, or (iii) profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects concerning the consumer.
(b)
If you are a resident of Colorado, you may exercise these rights by contacting us at
support@global.netease.com
. We may request information from you to verify your identity; for example, we may ask you to login to your account with us or ask you to provide information that we have on file and which we can use to authenticate you. You may also designate an authorized agent to submit a request to exercise your rights on your behalf; in this case, we may ask you for information to verify your identity and that you have authorized the agent to act on your behalf.
(c)
If we decline to take an action regarding your request, we will inform you of such, including the justification for declining to take action and instructions on how to appeal the decision. We will inform you of any action or inaction taken in response to such appeal. If the appeal is denied, you may contact the Colorado Attorney General to submit a complaint.
